"title": "5350: injustice, hated by God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5350",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's hatred of injustice is seen in his vindication of its victims, his solemn warnings, his penalties against the guilty and his commands to his people to renounce it.</p>\n<h2>God hates injustice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:19\">PRO 6:16–6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:22\">PRO 12:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a></p>\n<h2>God will vindicate the victims of injustice</h2>\n<h3>They cry for justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:1\">PSA 43:1</a></strong> <em>There are some OT passages where vengeance upon persecutors is called for (e.g., <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:1-Ps35:8\">Ps 35:1–8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:22-Ps69:28\">Ps 69:22–28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:18-Jer11:20\">Jer 11:18–20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:19-Jer18:23\">18:19–23</a>). These are called “imprecatory”. They arose from zeal for God's honour and from the desire for moral stability in society. They reflect an under-developed view of God's ultimate judgments and the failure to distinguish between the guilty and their innocent families. In the light of the NT the motives behind these prayers may be applauded but it is recognised that now they are best expressed in the denunciation of injustice accompanied by gospel witness, through which the hearts of oppressors are changed, leaving the matter of judgment as God's prerogative alone.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:4-Neh4:5\">NEH 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:1-Ps94:7\">PSA 94:1–94:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:10\">REV 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25\">JOB 19:25</a> <em>In OT times a redeemer was a near relative responsible for securing the just rights of a poor kinsperson.</em></p>\n<h3>God will answer their cry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:1-Luke18:8\">LUK 18:1–18:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:5\">PSA 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:20-Ps94:23\">PSA 94:20–94:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:6-2Thess1:7\">2TH 1:6–1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:14\">2TI 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:20\">REV 18:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:2\">REV 19:2</a></p>\n<h3>God condemns injustice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:3\">ISA 10:1–10:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:19\">DEU 16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:3-Amos1:4\">AMO 1:3–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>God will punish the unjust</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:1-Mic2:3\">MIC 2:1–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:17\">DEU 27:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:19\">DEU 27:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:19\">1KI 21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:5\">PRO 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:28\">PRO 21:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11-Amos5:12\">AMO 5:11–5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:4-Amos8:7\">AMO 8:4–8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:1\">NAM 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:45-Luke12:461\">LUK 12:45–12:461</a>CO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:6-Luke6:8\">6:6–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:6</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:1-Jas5:6\">JAS 5:1–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>The apparent present success of the unjust</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:1-Ps37:2\">PSA 37:1–37:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:3-Ps73:11\">PSA 73:3–73:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:15-Ps73:17\">PSA 73:15–73:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:10-Isa26:11\">ISA 26:10–26:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:12-Hab1:13\">HAB 1:12–1:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's people must hate injustice</h2>\n<h3>Injustice forbidden by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:22\">PRO 22:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:16\">EXO 20:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21-Exod22:22\">EXO 22:21–22:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:6-Exod23:8\">EXO 23:6–23:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15\">LEV 19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:35\">LEV 19:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:14-Deut24:15\">DEU 24:14–24:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17\">DEU 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:9\">EZK 45:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:10\">ZEC 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:9\">EPH 6:9</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice should be renounced by God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:163\">PSA 119:163</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:7\">DEU 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:2\">PSA 82:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:27\">PRO 29:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:21\">COL 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice displaced by love</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:31\">MRK 12:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:10\">ROM 13:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:19\">COL 3:19</a></p>\n<h3>God's people must bear injustice patiently</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:7-Jas5:8\">JAS 5:7–5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:39\">MAT 5:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:44-Matt5:45\">MAT 5:44–5:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:7\">1CO 6:7</a></p>",
